<TEXT>
an army dental surgeon accused of 
dressing as a woman and performing in a bar frequented by 
homosexuals was dismissed from the service thursday and sentenced 
to nine months in prison 
a courtmartial board announced the sentence the same day it 
found col edward modesto guilty of eight counts of conduct 
unbecoming an officer 
the ninemember board acquitted modesto of two counts of 
indecent exposure stemming from allegations he exposed himself to 
women at several laundromats 
modestos attorney walter gerash said he planned to file a 
motion for a mistrial 
modesto was confined at fort carson and was scheduled to go 
friday to fort leavenworth where he is to serve his sentence fort 
carson spokesman maryl neff said 
a 17year army veteran modesto 43 was charged in april after 
he allegedly engaged in homosexual acts dressed in womens 
clothing and performed at a bar frequented by homosexuals 
modesto pleaded not guilty to the indecent exposure charges and 
twice offered to resign rather than face a courtmartial for 
violating the armys ban on homosexuality 
military regulations prohibit homosexuality in the ranks saying 
it threatens security and morale 
modesto is the highestranking officer to be courtmartialed 
under the homosexual regulations at fort carson in at least three 
years 
a father of three modesto testified wednesday that he made the 
agonizing decision to acknowledge his repressed homosexuality when 
he turned 40 he and his wife are estranged 
</TEXT>
