britain will reopen its embassy in tehran this 
weekend with a staff of five the foreign office said and iran 
will staff its reopened embassy in london with a similar number of 
people 
the five britons will fly to tehran on saturday and reopen the 
embassy the following day a foreign office spokesman said 
thursday speaking on condition of anonymity 
the two countries will not exchange ambassadors for the time 
being the spokesman said 
the move was agreed to at a meeting last month between douglas 
hurd britains foreign secretary and ali akbar velayati irans 
foreign minister 
iran broke diplomatic relations with britain 18 months ago over 
the salman rushdie affair 
rushdie the indianborn british novelist was condemned to 
death in february 1989 by the late iranian leader ayatollah 
ruhollah khomeini for allegedly blaspheming islam in his novel 
the satanic verses rushdie has been in hiding ever since 
