<TEXT>
the confrontation of multinational forces 
in saudi arabia with iraq in occupied kuwait has the makings of the 
largest tank battle since the classic world war ii struggle at 
kursk on the russian front 
several thousand german and russian tanks fought in that epic 
1943 battle a russian victory that marked the german ebb on the 
eastern front 
iraq has about 430000 troops in kuwait bolstered by an 
estimated 3500 sovietdesigned tanks ranging from the aging t54 
to the more advanced t72 
they face more than 300000 troops in the usled multinational 
force with a tank strength expected to reach 1800 by the end of 
the month 
this month marks the anniversaries of two other famous tank 
battles that helped change the course of wars el alamein in the 
egyptian desert in 1942 and israels armored thrust against the 
egyptians across the suez canal in the 1973 yom kippur conflict 
the british victory at el alamein in which several hundred 
tanks on both sides were deployed turned the tide against adolf 
hitler in the middle east that epic battle pitted british gen 
bernard montgomerys eighth army against the vaunted afrika korps 
of field marshal erwin rommel the desert fox 
the british 7th armored brigade the successors of montgomerys 
7th armored division known as the desert rats are now 
deploying in saudi arabia with their challenger 1 tanks 
the tanks may now be hightech leviathans but the tactics 
differ little from those used back in world war ii veterans of 
desert tank warfare say 
october is also the anniversary of the 1973 middle east war in 
which israeli armored columns crossed the suez canal and encircled 
the entire egyptian 3rd army in a classic tank operation 
an estimated 1200 israeli and egyptians tanks were involved 
the men who fought in el alamein and the 1973 conflict say one 
constant factor in desert tank warfare is the need for air power 
when montgomery took over the first thing he did was to move 
royal air force headquarters alongside his own headquarters said 
retired british army col michael jeffery who fought in the 
western desert campaigns 
if youve got air superiority you have freedom of action and 
to attack the supply lines which is also important at el alamein 
it was complete air superiority he recalled 
zev eitan who served in israels tank forces in the 1948 1956 
1967 and 1973 arabisraeli wars and a veteran of the suez tank 
battle noted in 1967 once we had mastery of the sky our air 
force could help and we just had to follow to exploit the success 
of the air force 
air superiority was also important in the 1973 war since in 
the desert you dont have so much cover he said 
eitan was a battalion commander in the 1973 conflict and is now 
a consultant at israels jaffe center for strategic studies 
the iraqi forces of saddam hussein are deployed in defensive 
positions behind a shield of antitank ditches earthworks and 
minefields 
the iraqis are master military engineers whose digin tactics 
were perfected during their 198088 war with neighboring iran 
for most of that war however iraqi tanks were used in a static 
role as artillery rather than in the running battles that western 
forces are trained to fight 
tanks of the multinational force include usbuilt m60s and the 
topoftheline abrams tank in several configurations as well as 
the desert rats uptodate british challenger tanks 
the multinational force tanks are generally far more advanced 
than those of the iraqis whose t54 is based on a 1947 soviet 
model 
technology makes a vast difference said jeffery ours is 
better than saddams 
providing air cover for the the multinational force tanks are 
hundreds of groundattack jets and tankkiller helicopters 
iraq also has hundreds of groundattack jets and attack 
helicopters but it is unclear how many could be used for armor 
support operations 
since iraq has a twotoone edge in tanks another major factor 
especially in an area where resupply is problematic is 
retaining control of the battlefield once the running clash of 
steel has subsided 
this is important in armored warfare because not all tanks 
hit are a total loss said eitan if you remain in control of 
the battlefield you can repair some of your tank casualties 
</TEXT>
