an antismoking group praised the environmental 
protection agency for reinstating a scientist who had been 
dismissed from an advisory panel under pressure from the tobacco 
industry 
the epa said wednesday that dr david burns of the university of 
california at san diego had been reinstated to a panel on the 
health effects of others smoke 
mark pertschuk executive director of americans for nonsmokers 
rights in berkeley calif said he was delighted with the 
decision 
i think it was the only ethical thing at this point that they 
could do he said to have given in to the tobacco industry 
would have been a horrible statement about the impartiality of the 
