the security council voted unanimously wednesday to rebuke 
israel for rejecting a un mission to investigate the killings of 
19 palestinian arabs in jerusalem the vote followed israeli prime 
minister yitzhak shamirs rejection of an appeal from president 
bush to allow the investigation 
it was the second time the united states turned against its old 
friend over the oct 8 incident on the temple mount 
the administration sponsored the initial security council 
resolution adopted unanimously oct 12 which condemned israel and 
directed un secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar to send 
investigators to jerusalem 
bush in his letter to shamir urged the israeli leader to 
reverse the israeli cabinets decision not to cooperate in the 
inquiry 
but shamir and israeli diplomats in jerusalem and in washington 
informed the administration the decision was based on two 
principles that could not be reversed us officials and other 
sources told the associated press on wednesday 
one was that the security council had already condemned israel 
so the inquiry could hardly be an openminded one the other was 
