<TEXT>
an army newspaper marking the 30th anniversary of 
a rocket explosion says the mishap killed 165 people including a 
leading general making it the worst known spacerelated accident 
in the soviet union 
the red star article on wednesday said a prototype rockets 
second stage was accidentally ignited on the launch pad causing an 
explosion that burned many of the victims beyond recognition 
secrecy has shrouded the accident at the baikonur space center 
ever since the explosion shot flames into the central asian sky on 
oct 24 1960 no official death toll or technical details of the 
accident have ever been released despite several articles 
describing the event 
a monument to the victims lists only 54 names and published 
obituaries claimed that field marshall mitrofan nedelin commander 
in chief of the strategic rocket forces died in an unrelated plane 
crash 
