three recently promoted police sergeants 
have lost their stripes because they failed to shed their flab and 
the fraternal order of police is fighting mad 
ive got 26 years on the job and since i got out of the 
academy nobodys checked my weight to see if i ate too many 
doughnuts fop president john shaw complained 
stephen guckin joseph mcgoldrick and john j harkins became 
sergeants in april after passing oral and written tests but they 
also signed agreements with the city to meet weight limits 
when the deadline came last week they hadnt made their weight 
objectives they were demoted to the rank of officer 
city officials said pay varies according to an individuals 
merit raises and other factors but that the demotions meant the 
three men probably went from about 34380 a year down to around 
31500 
the city was sympathetic but firm about standards that had been 
loosely applied for years 
nobody wants to penalize people who are on a promotional 
list said ralph j teti the chief deputy city solicitor 
theyve shown they have some qualities of leadership but you 
dont want to do anything thats going to endanger them either 
some police who were ordered to get rid of the pounds succeeded 
a new lieutenant two corporals and a detective met their goals 
another detective told to lose 46 pounds got rid of only 35 but 
kept his promotion because of the progress he had made 
guckin was told to lose 40 pounds and only lost 20 mcgoldrick 
was expected to lose 28 pounds and didnt lose any and harkins 
promised to lose 100 pounds and only dropped two 
guckin said he had lost nearly 50 pounds before his promotion 
getting his weight down to 280 pounds although it was a struggle 
to lose 20 more pounds since then he said he hopes to lose 20 
more 
mcgoldrick 41 a nineyear veteran of the force weighed 291 
pounds last week harkins 37 a 16year veteran weighed 313 
according to city officials 
the police department doesnt require routine physical 
examinations but teti said it eventually hopes to do so once or 
twice a year 
the weight standards have been in effect for at least 15 years 
teti said although police currently undergo medical tests only 
when they are hired or promoted or when they return to duty after 
long leaves 
teti said the citys weight standards are based on tables 
developed by life insurance companies rookies have to be within 20 
percent of their ideal weight veterans must be within 30 percent 
for example the guidelines allow a 6foot male veteran to weigh 
up to 244 pounds and a 5foot6 female veteran to weigh 207 pounds 
shaw still thought the program was unrealistic 
you cant walk over to a cop and say youre being promoted 
to sergeant and by the way you have to loose 80 pounds i know 
people do it on tv but that doesnt make it right or good for your 
health he said tuesday 
guckin 31 said he was surprised to learn about the weight 
requirement last spring 
these promotions are not handed to you he said ten years 
ago they hired me at one weight now they expect me to be less than 
that because i got promoted 
teti said the police department agreed to put the three 
policemen back at the top of its list for promotions and they will 
have a shot at the next openings for sergeant 
provided they make the weight minimums he said 
