in the violence in the khayelitsha black township about 25 miles 
east of cape town 
many residents of black townships oppose the local councils and 
consider council members collaborators with the whiteled south 
african government 
tension has been high in khayelitsha since last weeks slaying 
of momsa mapongwana the wife of an antiapartheid leader in the 
township 
