fighting 
the parliament voted unanimously thursday for a majorityvote 
election system instead of a proportional system aim reported 
the agency said the system would be a winnertakeall format 
instead of a proportional system in which parties receive the same 
percentage of parliamentary seats as popular votes received 
chissano told the assembly a majority vote system would make 
the process of governing easier since minority parties were 
likely to have less weight in parliament aim reported 
in presidential elections a candidate would be required to gain 
at least half the votes to win if no candidate gets half a runoff 
would be held between the top two finishers 
there have been no presidential elections and frelimo has been 
the sole legal political party since this southeast african nation 
gained independence from portugal in 1975 
the frelimo party was marxist but it has undergone reforms in 
recent years and officially dropped its marxist label last year 
the parliament also approved articles guaranteeing all citizens 
the right to freedom of expression and freedom of the press as 
well as the right to information aim reported 
the articles give reporters access to sources and protects their 
independence and they provide the right to set up newspapers and 
other publications however radio and television will remain 
governmentcontrolled 
