beach not far from where the ambassadors party was robbed and shot 
them one survived 
human rights groups have compiled long lists of atrocities 
including one at a soccer stadium july 6 when siad barres 
personal guard fired on a crowd that jeered the president 
diplomats and others say 109 people were killed 
aid from the united states once one of somalias main 
supporters and other western donors has been cut drastically 
because of the abuses making an already dismal economic situation 
worse 
somalias banking system has collapsed the only 
commercialsavings bank went broke because of unsecured loans to 
siad barres relatives and friends thousands of people lost their 
money 
an insurgent group called the united somali congress which 
began fighting just a year ago has become a major threat and 
controls must of central somalia it has attacked towns and 
villages within 50 miles of magadishu in recent weeks 
the somali national movement an older group roams the northern 
part of the country and omar joss a renegade army colonel stalks 
the south with 600 to 700 men he led in a mutiny last year 
nur said his manifest group as it has become known is trying 
to unite the armed bands and other opposition into one major 
resistance 
to characterize the situation and the hopes of somalians for 
change nur paraphrased charles dickens 
it is the best of times it is the worst of times it is a 
time of great expectations 
