an economic slowdown aggravated by a 
persian gulf oil shock has walloped winnebago industries inc and 
the pain felt by the manufacturer of motor homes is being shared by 
its neighbors 
when winnebago is in trouble so is its home town of forest 
city says paul jefson mayor of the north central iowa community 
before layoffs began in late september the company had a work 
force of about 2600 in the community of around 4300 
as problems began surfacing at winnebago earlier this year the 
city anticipated its tax revenues would drop off its important 
that we live within the means of the city it will affect us 
jefson said wednesday 
that means no new elaborate plans for public works although a 
sewer project will proceed as scheduled he said 
the problems will get worse later this week when winnebago 
announces an austerity plan 
the company already has laid off hundreds of workers and gone to 
a fourday work week at its factories the new retrenchment will 
mean layoffs for whitecollar workers said winnebago spokeswoman 
sheila davis 
jefson says a community meeting is set for monday night to 
establish a task force to help winnebago employees 
an industry analyst said winnebago appears to be taking the 
right steps to return to profitability once the gasoline price 
