factories of durable goods items such as appliances and vehicles 
designed to last three years or more fell 17 percent in 
september transportation orders plummeted 68 percent 
winnebago with products that sell for around 27000 and up 
was hurting before iraq invaded kuwait aug 2 and sent oil prices 
soaring it has been stung by high interest rates and an unsettled 
economic climate that sapped consumer confidence 
winnebago has reported five straight quarterly losses and had a 
record 178 million loss in the fiscal year that ended aug 25 as 
sales fell 23 percent from the previous year 
in may directors suspended semiannual dividends to 
shareholders in late september winnebago began layoffs and 
