but will not result in reductions in the activities by its direct 
sales force key research programs and customer support services 
unisys said it was looking into a broad range of asset sales to 
reduce debt which mushroomed as unisys borrowed to pay dividends 
when profits lagged in the 1980s 
unisys said it hired lazard freres and another investment bank 
james wolfensohn inc to explore the sales but it did not 
disclose what assets might be involved 
unruh said in a statement that it would be difficult but not 
impossible for unisys to achieve its goal of reducing its debt by 
600 million to 800 million by years end debt totaled 26 
billion at the end of the third quarter 
unruh said the quarters results reflect a weakening general 
business environment and the pronounced softness of demand in the 
worldwide computer industry 
order growth in the united states continues to be weak and 
orders have slowed significantly in europe in recent weeks 
reflecting customer concern about general economic conditions and 
about the middle east situation he said 
in these circumstances it is very possible we could post a 
loss for the fourth quarter instead of the gain we expected until 
very recently he said 
the restructuring launched in late 1989 wasnt sufficient to 
cope with the changing business environment unruh added 
despite the slump unisys said its timeplex computer networking 
business its defense unit and sales in asia and the pacific were 
doing well it also said cash flow had increased significantly over 
last year 
we remain confident of our course toward restoring the company 
to profitability and reducing its debt load he said 
for the nine months ended sept 30 unisys reported a net loss 
of 3482 million or 272 a share compared with a loss of 6733 
million or 475 a share in the same period last year revenue 
totaled 718 billion up from 713 billion 
</TEXT>
